M|Real|tx|500 emails → 100 opens (20%) → 25 replies (5%) → 8 positive replies (30%) → 4 meetings (50%) → 1 client (25% close). ~**0.2% end-to-end conversion** for average performers.
M|Perf|tx|1. **Hook tp** — Timeline hooks outperform problem hooks by 3.4x in meetings
M|Perf|tx|2. **Personalization depth** — Up to 250% more replies
M|Perf|tx|3. **Brevity** — 25–75 words optimal, 83% more replies under 75 words
M|Perf|tx|4. **Targeting precision** — ≤50 contacts per cg = 2.76x higher reply rates
M|Perf|tx|5. **Follow-up st** — First follow-up adds 49% more replies
M|Perf|tx|6. **Reading level** — 3rd–5th grade = 67% more replies
M|Perf|tx|7. **Send timing** — Thursday peaks at 6.87% reply rate
M|Decl|Repl|inbox saturation (10+ cold emails/week, 20% say none relevant), stricter anti-spam (Google's threshold: 0.1% complaints), AI em flood (more volume, less qual signal). Writing craft matters more, not less — gap btw average and excellent is widening.
M|Resp|- **|** Highest engagement at 8% reply, 50% open
