M|Indu|**Hi|** Nonprofits (16.5%+), legal (10%), EdTech (7.8%), chemical (7.3%), manufacturing (6.1%).
M|Indu|**Lo|** SaaS (3.5%), financial services (3.4%), IT services (3.5%).
M|Top |tx|1. **Too long** — 70% of emails above 10th-grade level. Under 75 words = 83% more replies
M|Top |tx|2. **Too self-focused** — "We are a leading..." signals sales pitch. Count I/We sentences
M|Top |tx|3. **No clear value prop** — 71% of decision-makers ignore irrelevant emails
M|Top |tx|4. **Generic templates** — {{FirstName}} isn't personalization. Recipients detect instantly
M|Top |tx|5. **Feature dumping** — "Great reps lead w/ problems" (Lavender). One proof point beats ten features
M|Top |tx|6. **False personalization** — "Loved your post!" w/o specifics is transparent
M|Top |tx|7. **Asking too much too soon** — 30-min call in first em = "proposing on first date"
M|Top |tx|8. **Pushy language** — "Act Now" stacking increases spam flagging by 67%
M|Top |tx|9. **No CTA** — w/o a clear nx step, momentum dies
M|Top |tx|10. **"Just checking in" follow-ups** — "I never heard back" = 12% drop in bookings
M|Top |tx|11. **Wrong tone for audience** — Founder ≠ RevOps lead ≠ sales leader
M|Top |tx|12. **Jargon/buzzwords** — "Leverage synergistic platform" → "We help you book more meetings"
M|Top |tx|13. **Unsubstantiated claims** — "300% more leads" w/o proof triggers skepticism
M|Top |tx|14. **Too many contacts per company** — 1–2 people = 7.8% reply; 10+ = 3.8%
M|Top |15. |" / "Fwd:" / countdown timers destroy trust
